Version 1.0

RELEASE NOTES

WHAT DOES THIS APP DO?
======================

Darktrace Connector for Splunk is designed to interface with a Darktrace (Core) appliance to display information about anomalous network behaviour.

This app is designed to take JSON Syslog input from a Darktrace appliance to display varying severities of security breaches on Splunk and link them to more detailed reports on the Darktrace Threat Visualiser allowing for seamless integration between a Darktrace Appliance and Splunk.

WHAT IS DARKTRACE?
==================

Darktrace (Core) is the Enterprise Immune System’s flagship threat detection and defence capability, based on unsupervised machine learning and probabilistic mathematics.

Powered by advanced machine learning, together with a new branch of Bayesian probability theory, developed by mathematicians from the University of Cambridge, Darktrace is the only genuinely self-learning cyber defense technology proved to work at scale. It is capable of detecting cyber-threats and anomalous behaviours that bypass traditional security tools, without prior knowledge of specific threats, or using rules or signatures.

Darktrace works by analyzing raw network data, creating unique behavioral models for every user and device, and for the relationships between them.

Leveraging its unique machine learning algorithms, Darktrace forms an evolving understanding of an organization’s ‘pattern of life’ (or ‘self’), spotting very subtle changes in behaviors, as they occur. These behavioral changes are correlated and filtered, in order to detect emerging threats and anomalies.

Darktrace is delivered as a physical appliance, which is easily and rapidly installed within an hour, at a SPAN or TAP port within the customer network(s). The appliance passively monitors raw network data in real time, without disrupting business operations, and provides instant visibility into all network activity, notifying of in-progress attacks or emerging anomalies.

REQUIREMENTS/INSTALLATION
=========================

1. Install Splunk Enterprise
----------------------------

If you haven't already installed Splunk Enterprise, download it at http://www.splunk.com/download. For more information about installing and running Splunk Enterprise and system requirements, see the Installation Manual (http://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/latest/Installation).

2. Install the main Darktrace Connector for Splunk
--------------------------------------------

Install or symlink the main app to the $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps folder. For linking use the ln command on Unix/MacOS or the mklink command on Windows.

3. Set Up the App to Receive Data
---------------------------------

Upon installing the app, a TCP listening port must be set up for direct interaction with the Darktrace Appliance, TCP input ports can be set up by doing the following:

    1) Login to your splunk instance.
    2) Click 'Add Data' either on the main page or under the settings heading in the toolbar in the top right of the screen.
    3) Click on 'Monitor'.
    4) Select the option 'TCP/UDP' on the left, make sure TCP is selected in the following screen and type in the desired port number. If you wish to only accept data from a single Darktrace Appliance on this port, put the IP address of this device in the 'Only Accept Connection From' field and click 'Next'.
    5) Select the 'sourcetype' to be 'darktrace' which should be under the 'Structured' tab.
    6) Set App Context to Darktrace then click 'Review' followed by 'Submit' to set the new TCP listening port.

For other input options, such as forwarding ports, please see the Splunk Documentation.


4. Set Up Darktrace Appliance to Send Data
------------------------------------------

To start sending data from a Darktrace appliance, use the settings in your appliances Threat Visualizer. Change the following config settings:

    Alerting
        JSON Syslog Alerts        True
        JSON Syslog Server        IP address of the computer the splunk app is installed on
        JSON Syslog Server Port   Port number (pick a higher number such as 5514 if the app not running as sudo)
        JSON Syslog TCP Alerts    True
        Legacy JSON Alert Format  False

5. Set Up FQDN for Visualizer Click-Throughs
------------------------------------------

The Darktrace Official Splunk App will generate clickthrough links, and also display the links for quick analysis. To ensure these links are set up properly, from /config on the Darktrace appliance change FQDN to the proper url of the Darktrace appliance.

E.g. https://<FQDN>/#model/00019

USAGE
=====

Darktrace Connector for Splunk is designed to quickly show the top alerts generated by the UI. The interface will highlight the most significant breaches in the traffic light color coding system, for quick actionable alerts. Clicking on any of the panels will cause the table on the bottom of all screens to auto-generate with model breaches based on the input/filter pressed. For instance, clicking on the RED portions for High Impact, will filter the table to look for scores between 75% and 100%, the high scoring models within Darktrace.

The recommended usage for the dashboard is to aggregate the model breaches within Splunk and quickly access the most interesting data within Darktrace via a quick through to the visualizer for further investigation. The table with the model breaches will link you through to the exact model breach.

The Latest Activity page will highlight the last 7 days that can also be easily filtered. These filters include timeframe, score, and model.

The Trending page will highlight the performance of models and the system overall for the last 2 weeks, highlighting actionable changes to models that may be necessary, or obvious devices that may need attention.


